<P>
   BUDDHISM _ The rise in Buddhism and Eastern religions among baby
boomers. Pegged to the Dalai Lama's visit. (Lomartire, Palm Beach
Post). 40. PRIESTS-COPS _ The man who founded the Georgia
Association of Chiefs of Police is not a policeman at all. He's a
Roman Catholic priest. And he was recently given an honorary
doctorate in criminal law for his work with police officers over
the last 45 years. In 1953, two young police officers responding to
a routine call at the Shrine of the Immaculate Conception invited
Monosignor R. Donald Kieran to ride with them. He did and he became
hooked. He is currently chaplain for the Georgia State Patrol, the
DeKalb County Police Department, the GBI and the regional office of
the federal Division of Alcohol, Tobacco and Firearms. We talk to
Kieran about his years of experience and his fascination with
police work, and with some of the cops he has befriended over the
years. (GWhite, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).BUDGET INFORMATION
