reliable than a human. By Duncan Graham-Rowe. 600 words. (slugged:
BC-ROBOTIC-BLOODTESTING-(NEW-SCIENTIST)-NYTSF) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; AN EXTINCT FLY'S EYE MAY IMPROVE SOLAR POWER &LR;  _ Solar panels
could be improved by up to 10 percent by mimicking the design of
the eyes of an extinct fly. A zoologist from Sydney noticed that a
pattern of ridges on the surface of the fly's eye could reduce
reflection and so allow panels to capture light arriving at very
oblique angles. By Liz Tynan. 500 words. (slugged:
BC-SOLAR-PANELS-(NEW-SCIENTIST)-NYTSF) &QL; 
