</P>
<P>
   ISRAEL _ JERUSALEM _ Long divided over how to share their small
land, the rift between Jews and Arabs has recently jumped
dimensions _ from space to time. (Kaplow, Cox News Service). WITH
PHOTO (mug).WASHINGTON/POLITICS
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-ODD-DC _ WASHINGTON _ If you've never seen the
7,000-pound, 21-foot, sandal-wearing bronze statue of Albert
Einstein, you haven't seen one of the most eccentric attractions
Washington has to offer. The same goes for the National Museum of
Health and Medicine, which boasts an exhibit of bone fragments from
Abraham Lincoln's skull, complete with a few strands of his hair
still attached. We have an entire museum dedicated to chess,
another to dolls, and a monument erected to the survivors of the
Titanic. (The ship, not the movie.) These are the best-kept secrets
in a town that has trouble keeping anything under wraps.
(Montgomery, Cox News Service). WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
