<P>
   HKN-GRETZKY-DAVIDSON (New York) _ John Davidson, the Rangers'
MSG Network and Fox analyst, never asked Wayne Gretzky about
retiring. Three times since last week, Davidson told TV audiences
with increasing certainty that the end was nearing for Gretzky. But
Davidson, the former Rangers goaltender who flies on the team
charter and usually sits with Gretzky, never directly asked Gretzky
if he was leaving. Their relationship is not quite journalistic,
but a bond between one former and one current player and a
connection between two savvy league personalities. By Richard
Sandomir. (725 words)
</P>
