<P>
   WASHINGTON NEWS (``w'' category)
</P>
<P>
   RESERVE-UNITS (Washington) _ The 33,000 or more military reserve
units that the Pentagon is expected call up for duty in the Kosovo
crisis are likely to be drawn mainly from the Air National Guard's
aerial refueling personnel at 19 bases across the country. By ERIC
ROSENBERG. (Already filed.)
</P>
<P>
   IRS-LONG (Washington) _ Jennifer Long, a Houston IRS agent who
was a star witness at 1997 Senate hearings into agency abuses, says
her managers tried to fire her, then withdrew the action after Sen.
William V. Roth Jr., R-Del., blasted the office and announced an
investigation. By DAVID IVANOVICH.
</P>
