<P>
   OCTUPLETS (Houston) _ The pink and blue balloons and streamers
in the yard announce something special inside the southwest Houston
home. But it's the city garbage can parked next to the curb that
tells the real tale. The container is bulging with empty infant
formula bottles, household trash and diapers. The story of the
world's first surviving set of octuplets is about multiples _ 60
diapers a day, 40 feedings taking a total of 14 hours. By LEIGH
HOPPER. (Already filed.)
