<SLUG> BC-CORRECTIONS-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR SATURDAY, APRIL 17
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Saturday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-KOSOVO-U.S.-NYT (moved on Thursday, Apr. 15)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Thursday, Apr. 15,
about the Pentagon's plans to ask President Clinton for the
authority to call up reservists and National Guard members
misstated at one point the amount of money the White House is
expected to request from Congress to cover the costs of American
involvement in the NATO campaign against Yugoslavia. As stated
elsewhere in the article, the request is expected to be for $5.9
billion, not $4 billion.
</P>
<P>
   BC-KOSOVO-MACEDONIA-NYT (moved on Wednesday, Apr. 14)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday, Apr.
14, about the Macedonian Government's fears that Yugoslavia is
trying to destabilize the country recounted the history of the
12,000 NATO troops in Macedonia incorrectly. Some 1,800 arrived
last October and the rest this year. They have not been there since
1995.
</P>
<P>
   BC-MURDOCH-TV-SPORTS-NYT (moved on Sunday, Apr. 11)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Sunday, Apr. 11,
about the News Corporation's growing role in regional sports
television misidentified the company that is working with the News
Corporation's Fox Sports Net unit to create a service called Fox
Sports Net Interactive. It is ACTV Inc., not Access TV.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
