<SLUG> BC-CAR-HARMON17-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Promotor Harmon retiring from racing
 &HT;    By Rick Minter
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Bob Harmon, one of stock-car racing's most flamboyant
_ and successful _ promoters is retiring after Saturday's races at
Nashville Speedway.
</P>
<P>
   Since he started in the mid-1950s, Harmon has promoted races at
more than 50 tracks, including Macon Raceway, Senoia Raceway,
Lanier National Speedway and Peach State Speedway in Georgia.
</P>
<P>
   His latest effort, at Nashville Speedway USA, saw him take an
operation that was nearly broke and transform it into the top short
track in the nation.
</P>
<P>
   But at 66, he says he's ready to rest.
</P>
<P>
   ``I've had my day in the sun, and I've enjoyed it tremendously,
but I just don't have the energy I used to,'' Harmon said.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
