u s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-ATL-BBN-BRAVES-NOTES1     04-16 0381
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-ATL-BBN-BRAVES-NOTES17 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Cather demoted to AAA
 &HT;    By Carroll Rogers
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   DENVER _ The Braves optioned reliever Mike Cather to Class AAA
Richmond to make room for John Hudek on the 25-man roster and to
give Cather some time to work on his control.
</P>
<P>
   Cather, who is coming back from rib extraction surgery, has
struggled with the location of his pitches, causing him to be used
sparingly this season. In four appearances, he has given up three
runs in 2.2 innings. Monday in Philadelphia he gave up a pair of
solo home runs _ to Alex Arias and Scott Rolen _ in one inning. He
managed to win the game but it was clear he was not pitching
effectively.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's disappointing,'' Cather said. ``You always see yourself
as a big-league pitcher, going back to the minor leagues isn't fun
for anybody. I'm hoping to capitalize on it.... It could be a
blessing. I know I'm going to get some innings. I've got to take
advantage of it.''
</P>
<P>
   This is the second year in a row Cather has started the season
on the Atlanta roster, only to be sent down. But this time he's not
letting it get to him.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't take it personally anymore,'' Cather said. ``I know
it's for the good of the team.''
</P>
<P>
   Cather said his arm feels fine, and his pitches are as live as
ever.
</P>
<P>
   ``I've just been inconsistent,'' Cather said. ``I've been
inconsistent with my breaking ball and the location of my
fastball.''
</P>
<P>
   Cather's opportunities to pitch in Atlanta were shrinking, so
he'll welcome the Richmond assignment in some ways.
</P>
<P>
   ``You can throw in bullpens until your eyes cross,'' Cather
said. ``Throwing in game situations is where you get your stuff
back.''
</P>
<P>
   Said Atlanta manager Bobby Cox: ``It may have been smart letting
him spend the first two weeks in Richmond. Maybe it's my fault.''
</P>
<P>
   The Braves placed reliever Kerry Ligtenberg on the 60-day
disabled list to create a spot for Hudek on the 40-man roster.
</P>
<P>
   Etc.
</P>
<P>
   Javy Lopez could have played Friday, saying he was completely
recovered from the twinge he felt in his lower back on Wednesday
night. ... Ryan Klesko is still plagued by a hamstring pull and is
not expected to return in this series.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
