<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TEN-FED-CUP-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MAJOLI DRAWS RUBIN FOR FIRST MATCH IN FED CUP 
</HEADLINE>
  (rk) 
 By   ROBIN FINN   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   Iva Majoli of Croatia decided she liked the luck of the Fed Cup
draw Friday in Raleigh, N.C. In the first of five matches Croatia
is playing against the United States this weekend, Majoli, the
32nd-ranked player, is scheduled to face No. 23 Chanda Rubin, the
last-minute replacement for the injured Lindsay Davenport.
</P>
<P>
   In the second singles match, third-ranked Monica Seles, who has
an 8-0 Fed Cup record, will meet 70th-ranked Silvja Talaja.
</P>
<P>
   A French Open champion in 1997 but struggling since then, Majoli
pronounced herself eager to test herself and her 2-2 record against
Rubin, a fellow baseline grinder whom she has not faced in more
than three years.
</P>
<P>
   ``I almost forget how she plays,'' said Majoli, who has a 14-6
Fed Cup singles record. ``It's a really big thing for Croatia to be
in the first division, and we're going to fight as hard as we can.
I think in the Fed Cup everyone can beat everyone.''
</P>
<P>
   While praising the city and its Raleigh Racquet Club, Majoli
expressed regret that Zagreb, Croatia, the original host city, had
been ruled out because of the conflict in the Balkans.
</P>
<P>
   ``Everybody was very excited to have American players in our
country, and we wanted to really welcome them, but circumstances
didn't allow us to,'' Majoli said. ``I'm feeling really sad for the
people, because I think they're all suffering because of the one
leader, Milosevic.''
</P>
<P>
   Billie Jean King, captain of the U.S. team, said she did not
expect the injury to the second-ranked Davenport, who has a
sprained tendon in her left wrist and cannot hit a two-handed
backhand without pain, to compromise the new home team's chances.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think Chanda is playing the best tennis of her life,'' King
said. Rubin has made a snail-like recovery from 1996 wrist surgery
but has already won a title, and defeated No. 1 Martina Hingis this
year.
</P>
<P>
   The singles pairings are reversed Sunday, followed by a doubles
match. Although Davenport has volunteered to play the doubles match
if the series is tied at 2-2, for now King has designated Seles and
Lisa Raymond to take on Majoli and Talaja.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
